      "writtenOn": "2017-05-06T14:14:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This might be a little more idiomatic as an enum, maybe even a full-blown C++ enum class:\n\nenum class FilterFlag : int {\n  Zero  \u003d 0x00,\n  None  \u003d 0x08,\n  Sub   \u003d 0x10,\n  Up    \u003d 0x20,\n  Avg   \u003d 0x40,\n  Paeth \u003d 0x80,\n  All   \u003d None | Sub | Up | Avg | Paeth,\n};\n...\nstatic inline SkPngEncoder::FilterFlag operator|(SkPngEncoder::FilterFlag x, \n                                                 SkPngEncoder::FilterFlag y) {\n    return (SkPngEncoder::FilterFlag)((int)x | (int)y);\n}\n\nI will admit having to define operator| manually and at a global scope is a bit of a bummer.",
      "revId": "3b42961481585e5d243ae90503ce79dca49f1c22",
